				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hi everyone just my 2cp for anyone thinking of starting a bard in the great world of eq. What people seem to forget is that this game is meant to be as real as possible. As you know life is not easy so neither should the game be. There are no best classes (and people who bang on about certain classes being the best are getting very boring), its all up to the person playing them, its up to you to make your character the best you can. Yes, classes have different abilities this is what makes them different and original. A bard is a bard, nothing else, its not a mix of other classes, (if you want warrior skills choose a warrior).<BR>
But back too it, having a bard is not easy (see above) but i can certainly say it is fun and it is a challenge. We have many different abillities which if used correctly can lead you to glory.<BR>
If your the type of person that enjoys a challenge and doesn't just want the easiest route to the top, choose a bard, and if you accept the challenge, good luck to you and most of all have fun.<BR>
Be safe.<BR>
Dallandara Spiritsong <BR>
lvl 22 bard<BR>
